t the Middle Ages, in the debates of the Reformation over the nature of predestination and grace, and again in the controversies over the teachings of Port Royal.This popular text is preserved in more than 180 manuscripts. In order to establish the text, those manuscripts fragments copied before the twelfth century have been used, a group amounting to around forty textual witnesses. This volume fills a major desideratum in the field of Christian Latin poetry and will be of interest to philologists, theologians, and historians of Late Antiquity and the Middle Ages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Latin.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 4aAugustine of Hippo. 4aAugustinus. 4aBildung. 4aMedieval Education. 4aMittelalter. 4aProsper Aquitanus. 4aProsper of Aquitaine. 4aTheologie. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / General.2bisacsh1 aHorsting, Albertus G. A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2016z9783110485394oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311033398540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033662740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110336627423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110336627.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016